column5: Only 18 more days until our trip with Fishmaster for those big cats. I'm marking them off on the calander and getting excited!   John, ALIE GOBY, HearingFish, Bitsmith2k, and myself will get a chance to hook up and enjoy our outing.  I'll be leaving Lindsay early that morning and have room for three passangers, anyone want me to pick them up along the way? If so, send me your address and phone number.  Fishmaster, what time do you want us there? What should we bring? What is supplied?

Hi Cliff, hope you are well. We can take this to PM if you like but if you want to take a small detour off the highway in Burlington we could drive down from there together. Depending on what time we are expected we might even be able to grab a quick breakfast.  Really looking forward to it. Looks like it will be my first time on the water this year.  J...
Have a wonderful time gentlemen.....look forward to the pictures!
was gonna send ya a PM today Cliff to see if you were getting fired up yet.. guess the thread speaks for itself cant wait!
Well I'm excited for your Cliff  I hope you have just a super time, and you'd better be bringing your camera bud  Joey

John, PM your address and phone number, I'd be happy to swing by and pick you up! We'll make sure we have time to grab breakfast, one look at me and you'll know I don't miss a chance to eat very often!
HI guys Id love to come grab a spot fishing for cats!
channel cats are fun,  have a good time
You guys should start work out your arm muscles, pump some iron, sore arms are a gurantee. Better prepared! Enjoy your trip!

Thank you ladies, only thing that could make this trip better is if we had you along  fishinFanatic69; while we'd love to have you along, this is a charter that we booked a while back and space is limited. If you are interested in getting out for some of those big cats though, you should contact Fishmaster, he will help you out!
So who's running the camera boat for this expedition?
